OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779811864
OL,3,CMore temperature records could tumble
OL,4,Cafter scorching bank holiday
OL,6,FMore records could be broken on
OL,7,FTuesday after the UK experienced its
OL,8,Fhottest May day of all time.
OL,10,FThe UK also recorded its provisional
OL,11,Fall-time hottest meteorological spring
OL,12,Ftemperature when Kew Gardens in south-
OL,13,Fwest London hit 34.8C.
OL,15,FThe Met Office listed 12 locations
OL,16,Fwhere the record was topped on Monday
OL,17,F` ranging from Suffolk to Berkshire to
OL,18,FWarwickshire ` while 97 of its sites
OL,19,Freached or surpassed 30C.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
