PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779811864
OL,3,CMore temperature records could tumble
OL,4,Cafter scorching bank holiday
OL,6,FUntil that day, the all-time May peak
OL,7,Fstood at 32.8C reached in 1922 and
OL,8,F1944.
OL,10,FTemperature records are usually broken
OL,11,Fby just tenths of a degree.
OL,13,FThe expected high for large swathes of
OL,14,Fsouthern England and Wales on Tuesday
OL,15,Fis 35C ` which could creep up to 36C,
OL,16,Fsenior Met Office meteorologist Becky
OL,17,FMitchell said.
OL,19,FThose forecasts span the Midlands, the
OL,20,Fsouth-east and south-west England,
OL,21,FEast Anglia, and South Wales.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
