OL,3,CMore temperature records could tumble
OL,4,Cafter scorching bank holiday
OL,6,FWales also provisionally beat its May
OL,7,Frecord as Hawarden Airport reached
OL,8,F32.2C, with the previous peak measured
OL,9,Fat 30.6C in 1944.
OL,11,FThe UK Health Security Agency (UKHSA)
OL,12,Fissued its first amber health alert of
OL,13,F2026 on Friday, warning that there is
OL,14,Fa risk of a significant impact across
OL,15,Fhealth and social care services. The
OL,16,Falert will remain in place until
OL,17,FWednesday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779811864
OL,3,CMore temperature records could tumble
OL,4,Cafter scorching bank holiday
OL,6,FMeanwhile the AA warned that the
OL,7,Finterior of vehicles can reach 60C on
OL,8,Fa day when the outside temperature is
OL,9,F27C.
OL,11,FThe heat is considered to be dangerous
OL,12,Ffor some vulnerable groups including
OL,13,Folder adults as their bodies struggle
OL,14,Fto regulate temperature.
OL,16,FAge UK recommended staying inside
OL,17,Fduring the hottest hours of the day,
OL,18,Fbetween 11am and 3pm, and having
OL,19,Fregular cold baths or showers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/13
